www.huggingface.co
you can only *serve* huggingface models for now, where you can use a pre-trained model and use it in the advanced_server
What is serving exactly? How does it differ from training the template model?

training actually trains a neural network from scratch. the template miner is just a very basic neural network that is trained on Bittensor by learning from its peers -- by exchanging learning information with them.

serving is actually an already-trained model (called a pre-trained model) that can "serve" on the network by helping other miners learn. It gets a fraction of a tao each time it sets weights just like the regular miner
